Additionally, the formation of TPA-Cys Schiff base was also confirmed by examining 1H NMR (400 MHz, DMSO) spectra of pure Cys and TPA-Cys Schiff base. Fig. S3a-b in Supporting Information shows the characteristic peaks at 3.10–3.30 δ (ppm) (CH2
                        ), 1.23 δ (ppm) (SH), 4.23 δ (ppm) (CH) and 8.44 δ (ppm) (NH2) confirm that Cys has active functional groups. Fig. S3b in Supporting Information shows 1H NMR (400 MHz, D2O) spectrum of TPA-Cys Schiff base, exhibiting peaks at 3.09 and 3.34 δ (ppm) (CH2
                         protons), 4.70 δ (ppm) (CH-proton). Similarly, several peaks at 7.36–7.98 δ (ppm) (CCH aromatic ring protons) and the peak at 8.02 δ (ppm) (CHN- imine proton). Importantly, amine group peak of Cys was not observed around 8 to 10 δ (ppm) in 1H NMR spectrum of TPA-Cys Schiff base, confirming the formation of TPA-Cys Shiff base via the reaction between amine group of Cys and aldehyde group of TPA.

The size of synthesized TPA-Cys-MoNCs was characterized by HR-TEM (Fig. 2
                        ), and it was observed that the as-synthesized TPA-Cys-MoNCs exhibited spherical shape (Fig. 2a). The average size of TPA-Cys-MoNCs was calculated from the histogram (Fig. 2d) which was found to be ∼ 2.63 ± 0.55 nm. As shown in Fig. 2b, HR-TEM image shows the lattice fringes of MoNCs at 2 nm scale bar. Further, XPS analysis was carried out for the confirmation of oxidation state of core Mo in TPA-Cys-MoNCs. Fig. 3
                        a shows the XPS spectrum of a full scan of TPA-Cys-MoNCs, indicating the presence of Mo, S, C, N and O elements in TPA-Cys-MoNCs. Fig. 3b shows the high resolution XPS spectrum of Mo 3d of TPA-Cys-MoNCs. The binding energies at 231.02, 227.64 and 225.07 eV correspond to Mo 3d3/2 and Mo 3d5/2, which confirms the presence of two different oxidation states of Mo2+ and Mo0 in TPA-Cys-MoNCs [35,36]. Fig. 3c shows the high resolution XPS spectrum of S 2p of TPA-Cys-MoNCs. The two peaks at 160.52 and 166.01 eV confirms that the binding of thiol group with the surface of MoNCs.
